---
import HomeLayout from '../../layouts/HomeLayout.astro';
---

<HomeLayout
  title="Zebin Li | LLM Inference Infrastructure"
  description="Zebin Li's personal website. LLM Inference Infra Engineer at MiniMax, focused on KVCache storage, scheduling, and systems infrastructure."
  lang="en"
  currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}
>
  <div class="page-shell">
    <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
      <div class="hero-copy reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">LLM Inference Infrastructure</p>
        <h1 id="hero-title">
          <span class="hero-line">Make context</span>
          <span class="hero-line hero-gradient">flow smarter.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          I'm Zebin Li, an LLM Inference Infra Engineer at MiniMax. I work on KVCache storage, scheduling, and systems efficiency.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="primary-button" href="#work">Explore my work</a>
          <a class="text-link" href="#writing">Read my writing <span aria-hidden="true">›</span></a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-contact">
          <div class="hero-contact-status">
            <span class="availability-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>Open to connect</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-contact-links">
            <button
              class="inline-email copy-email"
              type="button"
              data-email="hellolizebin@foxmail.com"
              data-copy-label="Copy"
              data-copied-label="Copied"
            >
              <span class="contact-kind">Email</span>
              <span class="email-address">hellolizebin@foxmail.com</span>
              <span class="copy-label" aria-live="polite">Copy</span>
            </button>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/zebin-li/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">LinkedIn ↗</a>
            <a href="https://x.com/Zebin_Li98" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">X ↗</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-note">MiniMax · Shanghai Jiao Tong University IPADS · Shanghai</p>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-visual reveal" aria-label="A tiered KVCache system spanning HBM, DRAM, and SSD">
        <div class="cache-stage" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="cache-layer cache-layer--hbm"><strong>HBM</strong><small>Fast</small></div>
          <div class="cache-layer cache-layer--dram"><strong>DRAM</strong><small>Shared</small></div>
          <div class="cache-layer cache-layer--ssd"><strong>SSD</strong><small>Persistent</small></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="work" class="section-block" aria-labelledby="work-title">
      <header class="section-intro reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Selected Work</p>
        <h2 id="work-title">Turning systems problems into working infrastructure.</h2>
        <p>From tiered KVCache to DPU virtualization, I explore system boundaries and make them useful for real workloads.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="project-grid">
        <a class="project-card project-card--wide reveal" href="/kvcache-en/">
          <div class="project-copy">
            <p class="project-kicker">KVCache Infrastructure</p>
            <h3>Unified storage. Cache-aware scheduling.</h3>
            <p>A framework-independent service that manages KVCache across DRAM and SSD while exposing global metadata to the scheduler.</p>
            <span class="card-link">Explore the project <span aria-hidden="true">›</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="fabric-visual" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="fabric-ring"></span>
            <span class="fabric-ring"></span>
            <span class="fabric-ring"></span>
            <span class="fabric-core">KVCache</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="project-card metric-card reveal" href="/blog-dv4-pro-kvcache-en/">
          <div class="project-copy">
            <p class="project-kicker">Model Analysis</p>
            <h3>Inside DeepSeek-V4-Pro KVCache</h3>
            <span class="card-link">Read the derivation <span aria-hidden="true">›</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="metric" aria-hidden="true">10.2 KB<small>per token · 24× compression</small></div>
        </a>

        <a class="project-card dpu-card reveal" href="/dpu-kata-en/">
          <div class="project-copy">
            <p class="project-kicker">Cloud Virtualization</p>
            <h3>Offloading Kata Runtime to the DPU</h3>
            <span class="card-link">Explore the project <span aria-hidden="true">›</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="dpu-chip" aria-hidden="true">DPU</div>
        </a>

        <div class="compact-work reveal">
          <article>
            <h3>Titanium</h3>
            <p>A lightweight VMM in TrustZone using ARMv8.4 SEL2, implemented in both C and Rust.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>IOMMU Performance</h3>
            <p>Improving NUMA placement for IOMMU page tables in SR-IOV and VFIO environments.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="writing" class="section-block" aria-labelledby="writing-title">
      <header class="section-intro reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Writing & Talks</p>
        <h2 id="writing-title">Making complex systems clear.</h2>
        <p>Notes, derivations, and practical lessons from model inference, KVCache, and systems infrastructure.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="writing-grid">
        <a class="article-card article-card--accent reveal" href="/blog-dv4-pro-kvcache-en/">
          <p class="article-meta">May 2026 · Model Analysis</p>
          <h3>How much KVCache does DeepSeek-V4-Pro need per token?</h3>
          <p>Deriving the 10.2 KB/token footprint and its 24× compression ratio from model architecture.</p>
          <span class="card-link">Read the article <span aria-hidden="true">›</span></span>
        </a>

        <article class="talk-card reveal">
          <p class="article-meta">March 2026 · vLLM Meetup</p>
          <h3>KVCache Practices at MiniMax</h3>
          <p>From Traffic Characteristics to Architectural Insights.</p>
          <a class="talk-mark" href="/kvcache-practices-minimax.pdf" target="_blank" aria-label="Open the talk PDF">↗</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="experience" class="section-block" aria-labelledby="experience-title">
      <header class="section-intro reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Experience</p>
        <h2 id="experience-title">From systems research to inference infrastructure.</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="experience-card reveal">
        <div class="experience-summary">
          <h3>Following efficiency all the way down the stack.</h3>
          <p>My work spans LLM inference, cloud infrastructure, secure containers, and operating systems.</p>
        </div>
        <ol class="timeline">
          <li>
            <time>Oct 2025 — Present</time>
            <div class="timeline-content"><h4>MiniMax</h4><p>LLM Inference Infra Engineer · KVCache storage and scheduling</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <time>Mar 2023 — Oct 2025</time>
            <div class="timeline-content"><h4>ByteDance</h4><p>DPU Kata Container and secure container virtualization</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <time>Sep 2020 — Mar 2023</time>
            <div class="timeline-content"><h4>SJTU · IPADS</h4><p>M.S. in Software Engineering, advised by Prof. Haibo Chen and Prof. Yubin Xia</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <time>Sep 2016 — Jun 2020</time>
            <div class="timeline-content"><h4>Nanjing University</h4><p>B.S. in Software Engineering</p></div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="section-block" aria-label="About me">
      <div class="about-grid">
        <article class="about-card reveal">
          <div class="about-profile">
            <img src="/avatar.jpg" alt="Zebin Li" width="68" height="68" />
            <div><strong>Zebin Li</strong><span>LLM Inference Infra · ENFJ</span></div>
          </div>
          <h2>Engineering brings research into the real world.</h2>
          <p>I care about making high-performance systems understandable, dependable, and useful for real workloads.</p>
          <a class="text-link" href="https://ipads.se.sjtu.edu.cn/zh/pub/members/zebin_li/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">IPADS profile <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
        </article>

        <article class="knowledge-card reveal">
          <p class="project-kicker">Personal Knowledge Base</p>
          <h2>Keep learning. Keep sharing.</h2>
          <p>Technical notes and research summaries across KVCache, LLM inference systems, container virtualization, and operating systems.</p>
          <a class="text-link" href="https://ima.qq.com/wiki/?shareId=899dcecbd10c666a927221b325413d03cf917fc0839232da6fa71b0e1c6497fd" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Explore the knowledge base <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="site-footer" id="contact">
      <div class="contact-panel reveal">
        <div class="contact-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Stay in touch</p>
          <h2>Let's talk systems and inference.</h2>
          <p>I'm always open to conversations about KVCache, LLM infrastructure, and high-performance systems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="contact-methods">
          <button
            class="contact-method copy-email"
            type="button"
            data-email="hellolizebin@foxmail.com"
            data-copy-label="Click to copy"
            data-copied-label="Email copied"
          >
            <span class="contact-method-copy"><small>Email</small><strong>hellolizebin@foxmail.com</strong></span>
            <span class="method-action copy-label" aria-live="polite">Click to copy</span>
          </button>
          <a class="contact-method" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/zebin-li/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            <span class="contact-method-copy"><small>LinkedIn</small><strong>Zebin Li</strong></span>
            <span class="method-action">View profile ↗</span>
          </a>
          <a class="contact-method" href="https://x.com/Zebin_Li98" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            <span class="contact-method-copy"><small>X</small><strong>@Zebin_Li98</strong></span>
            <span class="method-action">Follow updates ↗</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-bottom">
        <span>© 2026 Zebin Li · Shanghai, China</span>
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/cutelizebin" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
          <a href="#">Back to top ↑</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</HomeLayout>
